# Market Digest — System Overview

## Purpose
A daily market intelligence system producing structured research across equities, macro, crypto, bonds, commodities, forex, and international markets. Uses a 7-phase pipeline where each phase builds on the previous.

## 7-Phase Pipeline
| Phase | Name | Skill File | Reads From |
|-------|------|-----------|------------|
| 1 | Alternative Data | `skills/premarket-pulse/SKILL.md` + alt-data skills | External feeds |
| 2 | Institutional Intel | `skills/inst-institutional-flows/SKILL.md` + `skills/inst-hedge-fund-intel/SKILL.md` | Phase 1 outputs |
| 3 | Macro Regime | `skills/macro/SKILL.md` | Phases 1-2 + memory |
| 4 | Asset Classes | bonds/commodities/forex/crypto/intl skills | Phase 3 macro |
| 5 | Equities + Sectors | `skills/equity/SKILL.md` + 11 sector skills | Phases 3-4 |
| 6 | Earnings & Events | `skills/earnings/SKILL.md` | Phases 3-5 |
| 7 | Synthesis | `skills/digest/SKILL.md` | All phases |

## Critical Files
- `skills/orchestrator/SKILL.md` — read this FIRST for any full session
- `config/watchlist.md` — tracked assets
- `config/preferences.md` — trading style + active theses
- `memory/BIAS-TRACKER.md` — daily cross-asset bias (14-column table)
- `AGENTS.md` — cross-platform behavioral rules

## Behavioral Rules
- **Always** read `config/` files at session start
- **Always** read corresponding `memory/*/ROLLING.md` before writing research
- **Never** delete or rewrite memory file history
- **Never** edit `outputs/daily/` files manually
- Output paths: `outputs/daily/{{DATE}}/` — use `{{DATE}}` placeholder

## macOS Critical
Use `sed -i ""` not `sed -i` — macOS BSD sed requires the extension argument.
